@DamageIncM:
Yes, like u said, upscaling doesn't mean "high quality". Upscaling is a method that u must sacrifice some little details to trade for something sharper and cleaner. Because of that, it would be kind of bad if the film being upscaled is live-action or anime full of small details. But I guarantee u that no scenes in this upscaled release is out of place or weird.

And yes, give this one a try and compare which one is more beautiful on your monitor / worth saving to your disk space. U are free to decide, buddy.

